                        <pb facs="d660-4" n="4" type="facsimile" xml:id="d660-4"/>
                        <p rend="sectiontitleital"><hi rend="roman">d)</hi> Strategic
                            Commodities</p>
                        <p>We are continually endeavoring to halt the flow of strategic commodities
                            which formerly were supplied to a great extent by the United <pb facs="1866" n="1691" type="typeset" xml:id="pg_1691"/> States to
                            Cuba. We have recently through the combined efforts of State, Commerce
                            and private industry successfully blocked the exportation of 500 small
                            tractors from Britain to Spain to Cuba and the sale of 2.5 million tons
                            of Egyptian oil.</p>
                        <p>Additionally, several shipments of bright stock (oil additive) have been
                            denied Cuba. In several instances export sales of Cuban sugar were
                            blocked.</p>
                        <p>Efforts to further disrupt Cuba’s economy through cutting off needed
                            imports and prevent the earning of badly needed foreign exchange by
                            reducing sales of sugar, tobacco, molasses and other products are being
                            carried forward on a continuing basis.</p>
